This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) using only unlabeled data and named entity dictionaries. It proposes a novel positive-unlabeled (PU) learning algorithm to perform the task. The paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks. It also involves machine learning techniques, which makes it relevant to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper focuses on named entity recognition, which is a sub-task of NLP, and hence, it could also belong to the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
